{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d84-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1476"},"text":"§ 1476.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Death gratuity: death after discharge or release from duty or training","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d85-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d86-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1480"},"text":"section 1480 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary concerned shall pay a death gratuity to or for the survivors prescribed in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1477"},"text":"section 1477 of this title","children":[],"tail":" of each person who dies within 120 days after discharge or release from—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d87-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" active duty; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d88-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" inactive-duty training (other than work or study in connection with a correspondence course of an armed force or attendance, in an inactive status, at an educational institution under the sponsorship of an armed force or the Public Health Service).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d89-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A death gratuity may be paid under paragraph (1) only if the Secretary of Veterans Affairs determines that the death resulted from an injury or disease incurred or aggravated during—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d8a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the active duty or inactive-duty training described in paragraph (1); or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d8b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" travel directly to or from such duty.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d8c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For the purpose of this section, the standards and procedures for determining the incurrence or aggravation of a disease or injury are those applicable under the laws relating to disability compensation administered by the Department of Veterans Affairs, except that there is no requirement under this section that any incurrence or aggravation have been in line of duty.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d8d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1476/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" This section does not apply to the survivors of persons who were temporary members of the Coast Guard Reserve at the time of their death.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida8d68d8e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/32/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(32)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1452"},"text":"72 Stat. 1452","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661/dA/tVI/s604/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661, div. A, title VI, § 604(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3877"},"text":"100 Stat. 3877","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/dA/tXVI/s1621/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, div. A, title XVI, § 1621(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/1602"},"text":"103 Stat. 1602","children":[],"tail":", 1603.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida8d68d8f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida8d68d90-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"ida8d68d91-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"1476(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"1476(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"1476(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"1476(d)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1133(a).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1101(4)(D) (as applicable to 38:1133(a)).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1101(5)(D) (as applicable to 38:1133(a)).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1101(6)(B)(ii) (as applicable to 38:1133(a)).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1133(c).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1101(2) (last sentence, as applicable to death gratuity under 38:1133(a)).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"38:1101(6)(A) (clause (3) of 2d sentence, as applicable to death gratuity under 38:1133(a)).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-01/ch837"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 837","children":[],"tail":", §§ 102(2) (last sentence, as applicable to death gratuity under § 303(a)), 102(4)(D) (as applicable to § 303(a)), 102(5)(D) (as applicable to § 303(a)), 102(6)(A) (clause (3) of 2d sentence, as applicable to death gratuity under § 303(a)), 102(6)(B)(ii) (as applicable to § 303(a)), 303(a), (c), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/858"},"text":"70 Stat. 858","children":[],"tail":", 859, 868, 869."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “Except as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1480"},"text":"section 1480 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are inserted to reflect 38:1134(a). The words “to the survivor prescribed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1477"},"text":"section 1477 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are inserted for clarity. The words “on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1957-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1957","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as executed. The words in parentheses in clause (2) are inserted to reflect 38:1101(6)(A) (2d sentence). The words “active duty for training” are omitted as covered by the definition of “active duty” in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101/22"},"text":"section 101(22) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the word “criteria” is omitted as covered by the word “standards”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida8d68d92-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida8d68d93-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1621/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1621(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Secretary of Veterans Affairs” for “Administrator of Veterans’ Affairs”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1621/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1621(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Department of Veterans Affairs” for “Veterans’ Administration”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (a), redesignated subsecs. (c) and (d) as (b) and (c), respectively, and struck out former subsecs. (a) and (b) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(a) Except as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1480"},"text":"section 1480 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary concerned shall have a death gratuity paid to or for the survivor prescribed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1477"},"text":"section 1477 of this title","children":[],"tail":" of each person who dies within 120 days after his discharge or release from—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) active duty; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) inactive duty training (other than work or study in connection with a correspondence course of an armed force or attendance, in an inactive status, at an educational institution under the sponsorship of an armed force or the Public Health Service);","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"if the Administrator of Veterans’ Affairs determines that the death resulted from (A) disease or injury incurred or aggravated while performing duty under clause (1) or the travel described in subsection (b), or (B) injury incurred or aggravated while performing training under clause (2) or the travel described in subsection (b)(2).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(b) The travel covered by subsection (a) is—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) authorized travel to or from the duty described in subsection (a)(1); or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) travel directly to or from the duty or training described in subsection (a)(1) or (2) that is performed by a Reserve who, when authorized or required by an authority designated by the Secretary, assumed an obligation to perform that duty or training and whose injury was incurred or aggravated after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1956","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida8d68d94-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida8d68d95-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1986 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":" applicable with respect to persons who, after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", incur or aggravate an injury, illness, or disease or die, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661/s604/g"},"text":"section 604(g) of Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1074a"},"text":"section 1074a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"ida8d68d96-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of authorities, functions, personnel, and assets of the Coast Guard, including the authorities and functions of the Secretary of Transportation relating thereto, to the Department of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 468(b), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
